description: Is that decaf? Are you sure? If you've ever felt paranoid about whether you're really getting decaf, and making sure that you're not unwittingly setting yourself up for a sleepless night, Caffeindicator could be for you. Caffeindicator is a litmus-like indicator to test whether coffee is regular or decaf. But this isn't a stand-alone product, at least not the way it was pitched. The idea is to get these indicators printed on the sugar or artificial sweetener packets that you see at the coffee shop, restaurant, or diner. It would have been a good idea for distribution, since it takes advantage of how these packets are already ubiquitous. Unfortunately for the caffeine-averse though, this product still hasn't hit the market, even years after its Shark Tank debut. What was demonstrated on the show was a mock prototype, and the entrepreneur hadn't even yet begun to approach the sweetener packet manufacturers or estimating the cost of such an add-on feature.
title: Caffeindicator

description: Expensive beauty products get a little more affordable thanks to the Spatty, which helps ordinary people salvage 15% to 25% of their cosmetics. Without these handy little spatulas, you're likely throwing out as much as a quarter of the contents of your expensive makeup, eye cream, face lotion, and other beauty products. The Spatty comes in 6-inch and 12-inch sizes so it can reach into tight containers to rescue the contents that you've been unable to reach in and scoop out. Whether you're pinching pennies or just a conscious consumer, the Spatty quickly pays for itself!
title: The Spatty

description: If you don't like to swallow pills, you may feel like there aren't any wellness supplements out there for you. Marz Sprays came up with a solution. Their supplements are designed and packaged as oral sprays. Just a spritz in your mouth and you're good to go. Marz Sprays has five different sprays on offer: ReBoot, Restorative, C-Spray, Slim, and Juicy. C-Spray is their top-seller, a blend of Vitamin C, Vitamin B-12, Vitamin D, Echinacea and other ingredients chosen to boost the immune system. There are Marz Sprays to cover just about anything you might want out of a supplement. Sleep Spray helps you relax and have a restful slumber. ReBoot wakes you up with caffeine. Slim is formulated to help with weight loss. Meanwhile, Juicy is a more general multi-vitamin supplement that's designed to take in small, multiple doses throughout the day.
title: Marz Sprays

description: Mother Nature does it again! Eco Nuts is all-natural laundry detergent that grows on trees. Related to the lychee, soapnuts (also called soapberries) naturally produce a mild surfactant that can be used for laundering clothes. Used for thousands of years by people in Asia, where these shrubs and small trees are common, you can now purchase your own soapnuts for your own laundry! From Eco Nuts, you can purchase these soapberries ready to use, de-seeded and sterilized with no added chemicals. To use them, just toss a few Eco Nuts into the wash with your clothes, and let them do their work. Eco Nuts are certified USDA organic and reusable.
title: Eco Nuts

description: Possibly the most successful product in Shark Tank history, Scrub Daddy is a smiley sponge that packs real cleaning power. Dip in warm water to make Scrub Daddy soft and squishy, or run cold water over it to make it firm for those tasks that require a more muscle. Safe on non-stick cookware, china, wood, stainless steel, and counter tops, Scrub Daddy is your go-to sponge for cleaning. Its round shape makes it ergonomically friendly for those times you have to clean the inside of a bottle or container, while the Scrub Daddy smile is also a wonderful tool for easily cleaning spoons and spatulas.
title: Scrub Daddy

description: Focus Designs is the maker of the self-balancing unicycle, or the SBU for short. The SBU is a battery-powered unicycle with built-in sensors that keep the rider balanced and moving forward with no need for pedaling. The rider controls the SBU with just their natural leaning motions, and according to the company, it takes only about 20-30 minutes to learn. The SBU is strong yet lightweight, supporting over 300 lbs. on its mere 27-pound frame and accelerating to 10mph in just 3 seconds. The SBU reaches a max speed of 12.5 mph and can take hills of up to a 30% grade.
title: The SBU Unicycle
